President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has declared that the national emergency declared on September 14, 2001, in response to the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001, will continue for another year. This decision is in accordance with section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act. The declaration is based on the ongoing and immediate threat of further attacks on the United States. The powers and authorities adopted to deal with this emergency will remain in effect beyond September 14, 2023. This notice will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.